<title>AUSTRALIA: Austrim says has 52.2 pct of Hawker.</title>
<headline>Austrim says has 52.2 pct of Hawker.</headline>
<dateline>SYDNEY 1997-07-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>Manufacturing and investment group Austrim Ltd said on Thursday it has increased its stake in auto parts group Hawker Richardson Ltd to 52.2 percent.</p>
<p>Austrim said it purchased 4.1 million shares in Hawker on Wednesday, taking its holding to 19.2 million shares.</p>
<p>Austrim on Wednesday said it would not increase its A$1.86 bid price for Hawker, which represented a 40 percent premium to the pre-announcement trading price of A$1.34.</p>
<p>The takeover bid is due to close on August 7.</p>
<p>-- Sydney Newsroom 61-2 9373-1800</p>
